Pandas of the Sleeping Dragon

The giant panda of China is a familiar and much-loved creature to animal lovers around the world. But in the bamboo forests of Sichuan, China, there is more than one species of panda, as well as a number of other species unique to the area -- like the golden monkey, the tufted deer, and the bamboo rat, a specialist in starting from the bottom and eating its way up.
